complementary colors appear more vibrant and produce a strong visual contrast.

  Mixing two primary colors creates the secondary colorscyan (G + B), magenta (R + B) and yellow (R + G).
magenta is made with red and blue, and is the complement to green.

tertiary colors are the result of combining a primary color with one of its secondary color neighbors. For example, within the RGB color model, red (primary) and yellow (secondary) make orange (tertiary). This adds six more colors to a simple color wheel for a total of twelve.

 split-complementary color scheme. This scheme starts with a base color, then pairs it with the two colors that are adjacent to its complement
 
 cyan (G + B), magenta (R + B) and yellow (R + G).
 
 hsl(120,100%,50%);
 Hue is what people generally think of as 'color'.
 Saturation is the amount of gray in a color. A fully saturated color has no gray in it, and a minimally saturated color is almost completely gray. This is given as a percentage with 100% being fully saturated.
 Lightness is the amount of white or black in a color. A percentage is given ranging from 0% (black) to 100% (white), where 50% is the normal color.
 A shade of a particular colour is one of its different forms. For example, emerald green and olive green are shades of green. 色调 ;A tone is one of the lighter, darker, or brighter shades of the same colour.
 The hsl() option in CSS also makes it easy to adjust the tone of a color. Mixing white with a pure hue creates a tint of that color, and adding black will make a shade
 
 linear-gradient(35deg, #CCFFFF,#FFCCCC);
 repeating-linear-gradient(
      45deg,
      yellow 0px,
      yellow 40px,
      black 40px,
      black 80px
    );
